  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@vvo Long comment here :) \n\nWell, I understand your point. It's true that if you don't want to follow a tutorial or you already done it, there's no references to go look after. \n\nHowever, when discussing with @bobylito, I really like the idea to have a tutorial for styling that will follow the one of the getting started. It may not be for everyone, but It can be a way to show how you can style our widgets (there's a lot of ways to do it...) based on a simple example. Of course, for now without inline style to perform small customizations, I believe it's not that powerful. But it's definitely a feature that I think we need to add. \n\nIn the end, maybe we can have both: a quick tutorial and a reference guide? \nDo you think it will perform the same kind of jobs twice and this will be useless in the end? \n",
    "created_at": "2016-10-05T08:15:57Z",
